`PyFixest` specifies different regression models by Wilkinson Formulas via the formulaic package. This syntax should be 
familiar to you if you have used R's `lm()` or `statsmodels` formula API. Many ideas have been developed in the fixest package (multiple estimation syntax, the i-operator, sample splitting). By default, all formula options are available to all models available via the `pf.feols()`, `pf.feglm()`, and `pf.fepois()` APIs. 

## Basic Syntax

In the simplest case, we regress covariates `X1` and `X2` on `Y`. 

::: {#5eb4e1fb .cell execution_count=2}
``` {.python .cell-code}
fit1 = pf.feols("Y ~ X1 + X2", data=data)
fit1.summary()
```

