## Multiple Estimation Syntax

Last, `PyFixest` provides syntactic sugar to fit multiple estimations in one go. This is not only typing efficient but allows for performance optimizations via caching - if you fit many regression models on a fixed set of fixed effects and many overlapping covariates or dependent variables, and performance is poor, we highly recommend you to try out multiple estimations. 

For multiple estimations, we provide 5 custom operators: `sw`, `csw`, `sw0`, `csw0` and `mvsw`. In addition, it is possible to specify multiple dependent variables.

### Multiple dependent variables

Multiple depvars are expanded to multiple estimations: `"Y1 + Y2 ~ X1"` behaves like `"sw(Y1, Y2) ~ X1"`.

::: {#3260a40b .cell execution_count=16}
``` {.python .cell-code}
fit_multi_dep = pf.feols("Y + Y2 ~ X1 + X2", data=data)
pf.etable(fit_multi_dep)
```

